investigation.title: Bulk RNA sequencing and spatially resolved transcriptional profiling of cerebellums from mice flown on the RRRM-2 mission
investigation.description: In the Rodent Research Reference Mission (RRRM-2), forty female C57BL/6NTac mice were flown on the International Space Station. To assess differences in outcomes due to age, twenty 12 week-old and twenty 29 week-old mice were flown, respectively.

project.title: Rodent Research Reference Mission 2 (RRRM-2)/Rodent Research 17 (RR-17)
project.funding: The sequencing analysis was funded by NASA Space Biology Program Office, Space Life and Physical Sciences Research and Applications Division.

parameters.Sample Preservation Method: for spatial transcriptomics: right brain hemispheres were placed in OCT compound and placed on dry ice until frozen throughout; for bulkRNAseq: right brain hemispheres were snap frozen in liquid nitrogen
